latestPosts.caption:
Shades of love - Ishq de rang

“Rabb ne ohnu bnaya, mudke kuch ni banaya.
Ohdi yaadan che bss apan ishq sajaya.
mein labhdi firdi, mera dilbar jaani,
asi pyaar roohani karke v dard kamayaa.”

In a palette that gently fades from deep rose to the quiet blush of dawn, this lehenga speaks in silences only heritage can hold. Reimagined this year with Surbhi Jyoti, it’s a continuation of a story we first told in rust — but this time, it breathes differently.

The double-layered silhouette reveals a Banarasi base that peeks through like memory—familiar yet newly felt. Hand-embroidered elephants, camels, and peacocks roam across its canvas—not as symbols of grandeur, but as echoes of old-world Rajwada charm, lived and worn with ease.

This is not an outfit that shouts. It remembers. And in that remembrance, it becomes something intimate—personal. A quiet kind of celebration.

latestPosts.caption:
This wasn’t just a look. It was a feeling. A prayer in fabric. A love letter to Punjab — to where we come from, to what we carry, and to the ones who came before us.

@diljitdosanjh’s Met Gala 2025 ensemble wasn’t made in a studio. It was born in quiet rooms filled with calloused hands and timeless skill — where Sikh, Hindu, and Muslim karigars wove their faith, memory, and mastery into every thread.

This was more than fashion.
It was unity.
It was heritage.
It was us.

Executed by Team @pitambarabymanisha — held together by purpose, built on belief, and stitched with reverence.

We’ll carry this moment forever.

latestPosts.caption:
More than a look, this was history in motion and a love letter.
To Punjab. To memory. To the hands that still remember how to make beauty from thread.

@diljitdosanjh Met Gala 2025 ensemble was not just couture, it was cultural storytelling, stitched by Sikh, Hindu, and Muslim karigars from across India.

Team Pitambara: Executed by @pitambarabymanisha, assisted by @okopvi and creative directed by @hasil.in, this garment brought together endangered techniques, ancestral motifs, and sacred symbolism to create something bold, rooted, and reverent.

Big ups to @abhilashatd @forummmmm

From the embroidered map of Punjab in golden thread, to the sacred Gurmukhi script, to jewelry worn as resistance, this was not just fashion.This was history. This was identity. This was us.

Written with care by @harjaskgrewal
Designed and curated by @directedbyhasil

latestPosts.caption:
And WE MAKE HISTORY 🤩. Out of 307 looks, we stand out to be the most LOVED and the most ICONIC of all. What else could we have asked for? 🧿✨

@diljitdosanjh paaji, no one but you could’ve carried the weight of culture, pride, and representation on such a grand stage with this level of grace and power. Thank you for trusting us with something so monumental. 🧿

Endless gratitude to @prabalgurung and your incredible team for your unwavering belief in us — it means the world.

And to be honest, we are short of words because @abhilashatd & @forummmmm — you guys killed it. Couldn’t have been done better. 💥

Huge shoutout to @themanishashrma for taking charge of this and @hasil.in @directedbyhasil for directing the look with unmatched precision and soul.

TEAM PITAMABARA @okopo.xvi — you should be more than proud of yourself for pulling this off with such finesse and in no time.

THIS WILL GO DOWN AS A GOLDEN CHAPTER IN THE BOOKS OF HISTORY.

latestPosts.caption:
FOR THE MAIN MAN @diljitdosanjh 

What a surreal moment this is for TEAM PITAMBARA right now! Thankyou for the wonderful opportunity @prabalgurung and team 🦚🪷

We’re beyond grateful for all the love and support you’ve been sending our way — it truly means the world to us.

There’s so much more to share about the outfit, and we know you’re all eager for a closer look at the details. Don’t worry — we’ve got you covered!

Massive shoutout to everyone who played a part in bringing this to life. This wouldn’t have been possible without you.

Much love to Team Diljit for showing so much faith in us : @abhilashatd @forummmmm 

Huge shoutout to @themanishashrma for bringing the vision to life, working endlessly day and night to do the imposible given the time frame. Assisted by our most excited @okopo.xvi ✨

Big ups to @hasil.in for all the design details, creative direction and keeping the aesthetics in check. 

🎥 : @directedbyhasil 

And a big round of applause for our artisans who worked day and night for this project.

#pitambara #metgala #prabalgurung #metgala2025 #pitambarabymanisha #diljitdosanjh #bestfit #madeinindia

Time to shine a light on something truly special — our recent collaboration with @prabalgurung for **MET GALA 2025**.

What once felt like a distant dream is now part of our story: bringing our *art, craft, and culture* to one of fashion’s most iconic stages. And the cherry on top? Creating a look for the one and only @diljitdosanjh for the @metgalaofficial_ . Sounds wild, right? But yes — it happened. And we delivered.

Endless gratitude to @sohail__mughal___ and @stylingbyvictor for making us part of this incredible journey.

Massive shoutout to @directedbyhasil @hasil.in for their creative direction and input. And hats off to **TEAM PITAMBARA** @okopo.xvi — for pulling off magic with insane dedication and speed.

A heartfelt thank you to @forummmmm and @abhilashatd from Diljit’s team for their constant support.

This was more than fashion — it was a moment for *us*, for *our roots*, and for *the culture*.

#MetGala2025 #DiljitDosanjh #PrabalGurung #Pitambara #SouthAsianExcellence #CulturalPride #Pitamabarabymanisha #punjabiaageoye
